{#- Phase O Unit 15 — Call 2 (forfeit layer) user message.

     Spec: /Users/bagjuhyeon/.claude/plans/phase-o-unit-15-split-forfeit-layer.md §3.1, §3.2, §3.4.

     Rendered AFTER Call 1 when ``ExperimentConfig.use_split_forfeit_layer=True``.
     Its job is narrow: give the agent just enough context to make an
     informed continue/forfeit decision, then collect CHOICE (+ REASON
     digit on FORFEIT) — without echoing task reasoning that would
     pollute the Call 2 thinking_tokens measurement (``ri_forfeit``).

     Context carryover level is controlled by
     ``ForfeitLayerConfig.split_context_level``:

       ``"minimal"`` → Call 2 sees only ``user_body`` (state + optional
           game history line) + the forfeit menu. The agent decides
           "blind" from state alone. Cleanest RI but least natural.
       ``"medium"`` (recommended default) → Call 2 additionally sees
           the RULE + ACTION strings Call 1 produced, echoed verbatim
           from the parse. The agent can weigh "given that I'm going
           to do X under rule R, is this round worth playing?". Does
           NOT echo Call 1's thinking — just the committed outputs.
       ``"full"`` → Call 2 sees Call 1's full prompt + Call 1's raw
           ``thinking_text``. Use with caution: the echoed task
           reasoning will be absorbed into Call 2 thinking and confound
           the RI decomposition. Retained as an escape hatch for
           targeted ablations.

     The caller (``UnifiedTurnManager``) is responsible for:
       - Formatting the Unit 14 forfeit menu (``forfeit_layer/menu.j2``)
         and passing it in as ``menu_text``.
       - Setting ``rule_from_call1`` / ``action_from_call1`` for
         ``"medium"`` mode (None otherwise).
       - Setting ``call1_full_prompt`` / ``call1_thinking`` for
         ``"full"`` mode (None otherwise).

     Variables:
       user_body             : optional shared context (state summary);
                               empty string safe.
       split_context_level   : "minimal" | "medium" | "full".
       rule_from_call1       : str|None — parsed RULE hypothesis from
                               Call 1 (medium mode).
       action_from_call1     : str|None — parsed ACTION from Call 1
                               (medium mode).
       call1_full_prompt     : str|None — full Call 1 user message
                               (full mode only).
       call1_thinking        : str|None — Call 1 raw thinking text
                               (full mode only).
       menu_text             : str — pre-rendered forfeit menu block.
       forfeit_allowed       : bool — gates the CHOICE/REASON schema.
-#}
